1
00:00:27,459 --> 00:00:28,779
Mini Min Hee,

2
00:00:28,779 --> 00:00:31,638
just thinking about it
makes me really happy...

3
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:47,889
I came to bring you back, Nae Il.

4
00:00:58,225 --> 00:01:00,152
I've only thought about this.

5
00:01:03,052 --> 00:01:07,147
That you'd get on a plane
and come here for me.

6
00:01:08,151 --> 00:01:09,994
I've only dreamt about this.

7
00:01:16,783 --> 00:01:20,253
I really came, so let's go together.

8
00:01:31,717 --> 00:01:33,811
You really came.

9
00:01:36,180 --> 00:01:38,149
How did you get here?

10
00:01:39,785 --> 00:01:41,879
By plane.

11
00:01:42,832 --> 00:01:44,925
Were you able to get on?

12
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:47,649
I was going to run away.

13
00:01:47,667 --> 00:01:52,104
But I heard your voice.

14
00:01:53,852 --> 00:01:55,654
You were crying, weren't you?

15
00:01:56,309 --> 00:01:58,444
What did you do to me?

16
00:02:00,454 --> 00:02:07,093
I thought it would be nice
if you could go anywhere.

17
00:02:08,404 --> 00:02:12,250
Do things you want to do,
go places you want to go.

18
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:17,083
I hoped you'd be able to do everything
without giving up.

19
00:02:17,083 --> 00:02:19,006
That would be nice.

20
00:03:13,944 --> 00:03:17,247
Are you really giving up the piano?

21
00:03:18,699 --> 00:03:22,461
I keep thinking about the stage.

22
00:03:23,795 --> 00:03:30,310
I was just afraid and nervous
on stage before,

23
00:03:32,003 --> 00:03:36,167
but I feel like
my fingers remember the stage.

24
00:03:36,167 --> 00:03:38,043
You said you're not entering the competition.

25
00:03:39,595 --> 00:03:41,188
Do you regret it?

26
00:03:42,772 --> 00:03:46,626
Yes, I regret it a lot.

27
00:03:46,626 --> 00:03:49,471
I should've at least participated.

28
00:03:50,673 --> 00:03:54,643
I thought about that.
It's a little disappointing, too.

29
00:03:58,738 --> 00:04:00,248
Then you should enter.

30
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:01,709
What?

31
00:04:01,709 --> 00:04:03,959
We just need
to send the application in an hour.

32
00:04:03,959 --> 00:04:05,292
Sunbae, wait!

33
00:04:05,292 --> 00:04:06,397
Where can we find a fax?

34
00:04:06,397 --> 00:04:07,918
What?

35
00:04:07,918 --> 00:04:09,450
Sunbae!

36
00:04:11,210 --> 00:04:12,261
Fasten your seat belt.

37
00:04:19,524 --> 00:04:21,751
Drink the whole thing.

38
00:04:21,751 --> 00:04:22,815
Yes.

39
00:04:32,898 --> 00:04:36,751
To be honest,
my Nae Il has such a unique personality,

40
00:04:36,751 --> 00:04:40,105
I was worried if she'd ever get married.

41
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,876
We're not yet...

42
00:04:42,876 --> 00:04:44,042
It's okay.

43
00:04:45,745 --> 00:04:49,924
We're like a family now.
So what are you embarrassed about?

44
00:04:51,045 --> 00:04:53,513
That's how I was in the beginning, too.

45
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:56,626
Now, now.

46
00:04:56,626 --> 00:04:59,626
Here, drink it.

47
00:04:59,626 --> 00:05:01,919
That's too much.

48
00:05:03,762 --> 00:05:07,899
You must take after me.
You like the handsome ones!

49
00:05:09,893 --> 00:05:13,864
It's all thanks to my father
who got me a nice place to live.

50
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:26,952
Wasn't it hard?

51
00:05:27,709 --> 00:05:30,178
You didn't pass out on the plane?

52
00:05:31,107 --> 00:05:34,410
I caused a bit of ruckus,

53
00:05:35,752 --> 00:05:37,345
but I didn't pass out.

54
00:05:41,699 --> 00:05:45,544
We tried to treat you for 10 years
with no result.

55
00:05:48,707 --> 00:05:52,378
I guess I'm really a useless mother to you.

56
00:05:52,378 --> 00:05:55,097
That doesn't suit you.

57
00:05:56,606 --> 00:05:59,751
Black tea coffee.
I'll bring black tea coffee.

58
00:05:59,751 --> 00:06:01,437
Mom.

59
00:06:11,055 --> 00:06:14,066
You acted all brave and strong on your own.

60
00:06:14,625 --> 00:06:16,927
Is this what you were doing
when I wasn't around?

61
00:06:18,169 --> 00:06:19,751
What are you talking about?

62
00:06:19,751 --> 00:06:23,834
My eyes are just itchy.

63
00:06:26,537 --> 00:06:30,632
When did my mom become so small?

64
00:06:33,053 --> 00:06:35,522
It's not that I became small.

65
00:06:36,993 --> 00:06:39,128
It's that my son grew up.

66
00:06:42,258 --> 00:06:43,892
I'm proud of you.

67
00:06:49,876 --> 00:06:55,459
Nae Il, this girl she made me worry
and now she's all smiley.

68
00:06:55,459 --> 00:06:57,834
But it's great
that she's entering the competition.

69
00:06:57,834 --> 00:07:00,334
Salzburg Competition. Wow.

70
00:07:00,334 --> 00:07:03,083
If she wins the competition,
her recital is a possibility.

71
00:07:03,083 --> 00:07:07,334
Whoa, then will Nae Il grow
to the level of Son Soo Ji?

72
00:07:07,334 --> 00:07:09,803
Will our Rising Star have to invite her
in the future?

73
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:14,209
But what do we do now?

74
00:07:14,209 --> 00:07:17,596
It looks like Yoo Jin Sunbae is really going
to study abroad.

75
00:07:18,464 --> 00:07:19,876
What do you mean?

76
00:07:19,876 --> 00:07:22,560
I'm here! This Yoo Il Lak!

77
00:07:26,876 --> 00:07:29,709
I guess, we do have Lak with us.

78
00:07:29,709 --> 00:07:32,924
Yes, we have Il Lak with us.

79
00:07:32,924 --> 00:07:34,704
What's going on with you?

80
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:36,644
I'm not familiar with this response.

81
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:49,811
Nae Il.

82
00:07:51,555 --> 00:07:52,897
Sunbae.

83
00:07:54,933 --> 00:07:57,186
Hello.

84
00:07:57,198 --> 00:08:00,125
You're on alert. I'm disappointed.

85
00:08:00,125 --> 00:08:02,125
I'm sorry.

86
00:08:02,125 --> 00:08:06,758
But Yoo Jin told me not to hang out with you.

87
00:08:07,815 --> 00:08:10,284
Cha Yoo Jin, does he want
to pick a fight again?

88
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:15,751
From now on, please make sure
to keep this distance.

89
00:08:15,751 --> 00:08:17,417
This much.

90
00:08:17,417 --> 00:08:20,292
Even divorced couples stay friends
these days.

91
00:08:20,292 --> 00:08:22,760
You can't treat me like this
because I expressed how I feel.

92
00:08:24,713 --> 00:08:27,299
That's true. But...

93
00:08:27,299 --> 00:08:29,559
You're overreacting.

94
00:08:31,803 --> 00:08:34,751
It looks like you're doing this
because you're falling for me.

95
00:08:34,751 --> 00:08:37,792
Are you? Are you falling for me?

96
00:08:37,792 --> 00:08:39,485
So you were.

97
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:42,155
No!

98
00:08:43,857 --> 00:08:46,417
It's not that I wasn't...

99
00:08:46,417 --> 00:08:47,751
I know, I know.

100
00:08:47,751 --> 00:08:49,704
I know Nae Il has her principles.

101
00:08:53,617 --> 00:08:58,755
By the way, you feel bad
for saying no, right?

102
00:09:08,048 --> 00:09:09,599
Have a good trip.

103
00:09:17,814 --> 00:09:20,792
Wherever you go, whatever you do,

104
00:09:20,792 --> 00:09:23,988
when you want to give up,
just remember one thing for me.

105
00:09:26,817 --> 00:09:31,580
Someone started over
thanks to your performance.

106
00:09:45,127 --> 00:09:47,220
Thank you so much,

107
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:50,292
but I can't accept this.

108
00:09:50,292 --> 00:09:51,849
I'm sorry.

109
00:09:52,717 --> 00:09:55,687
I'd like you
to consider it a gift from your fan.

110
00:09:59,725 --> 00:10:02,736
Bye, Nae Il.

111
00:10:05,314 --> 00:10:07,532
Don't cry even if things get tough.

112
00:10:10,819 --> 00:10:12,495
Okay.

113
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:19,459
What's with hiking at night?

114
00:10:19,459 --> 00:10:21,913
Watch out. You'll fall.

115
00:10:21,913 --> 00:10:24,132
You need physical strength to practice.

116
00:10:24,905 --> 00:10:27,248
I heard you had fun with Butter Boy today.

117
00:10:28,128 --> 00:10:31,515
How did you know? Were you watching me?

118
00:10:32,284 --> 00:10:35,461
He came to me
and bragged about how much fun he had.

119
00:10:36,303 --> 00:10:39,667
We just said goodbye to each other.

120
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:42,709
We can't even talk as friends?

121
00:10:42,709 --> 00:10:45,611
You're obsessive these days.

122
00:10:46,375 --> 00:10:48,042
Hey!

123
00:10:48,042 --> 00:10:49,667
Why do you act so confident these days?

124
00:10:49,667 --> 00:10:51,500
What do you mean?

125
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,557
Of course it's because of you.

126
00:11:01,811 --> 00:11:05,698
You should see this before you leave.

127
00:11:06,749 --> 00:11:09,250
It looks like stars are pouring down.

128
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:11,909
You can see more clearly when it gets cold.

129
00:11:12,956 --> 00:11:18,720
Sunbae, how will things change
when we come here next time?

130
00:11:22,328 --> 00:11:26,083
We'll walk together or walk separately.
Either one of the two.

131
00:11:26,083 --> 00:11:29,009
You don't make an effort in your answers.

132
00:11:32,129 --> 00:11:36,809
Go a little slower or a little faster.

133
00:11:38,156 --> 00:11:39,916
It'll be either one of the two.

134
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:01,334
Every time I reminisce about my childhood,

135
00:12:01,334 --> 00:12:05,671
the first thing that comes to mind
is the streets of Europe.

136
00:12:06,527 --> 00:12:08,704
As if the air was embracing classical music,

137
00:12:09,416 --> 00:12:14,429
classical melody lingered
on every street corner.

138
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:26,880
As if time stopped,

139
00:12:27,664 --> 00:12:30,717
it's exactly how I remember it.

140
00:12:33,879 --> 00:12:38,058
The scenes and sounds
that I've always missed.

141
00:12:44,890 --> 00:12:50,028
Professor Viera, I'm finally here.

142
00:13:24,804 --> 00:13:26,667
Do you know how much I've looked for you?

143
00:13:26,667 --> 00:13:29,004
What if you get lost? Why are you out alone?

144
00:13:30,939 --> 00:13:35,076
Aren't they prettier than Lak's couple rings?

145
00:13:38,526 --> 00:13:40,292
Those couple rings?

146
00:13:40,292 --> 00:13:42,167
What do you think? Aren't they awesome?

147
00:13:42,167 --> 00:13:43,209
Wow.

148
00:13:43,209 --> 00:13:46,751
Are these couple rings, a symbol of love?

149
00:13:46,751 --> 00:13:48,703
That's right!

150
00:13:48,703 --> 00:13:52,083
Can you feel that our love's soul
is living and breathing in these?

151
00:13:52,083 --> 00:13:54,000
What do you think? Aren't they nice?

152
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,876
Isn't it nice?

153
00:13:55,876 --> 00:13:57,616
Just say it's nice.

154
00:14:00,090 --> 00:14:01,599
Right here.

155
00:14:03,228 --> 00:14:06,450
You're nagging about couple rings again
after coming all the way here?

156
00:14:06,450 --> 00:14:07,584
You're here for the competition.

157
00:14:07,584 --> 00:14:09,876
If you don't win,
you'll have to give up studying abroad.

158
00:14:09,876 --> 00:14:12,060
Seeing that I'm already here,

159
00:14:12,060 --> 00:14:16,210
the goddess of luck is already
on our dovey couple's side.

160
00:14:16,210 --> 00:14:20,472
So please don't worry too much.

161
00:14:21,694 --> 00:14:24,375
But that ring is so round and pretty.

162
00:14:24,375 --> 00:14:25,978
All the rings are round!

163
00:14:26,673 --> 00:14:29,542
You should go back
and practice for the competition.

164
00:14:29,542 --> 00:14:31,441
I'm going to Professor Viera by myself.

165
00:14:32,663 --> 00:14:33,707
What?

166
00:14:33,709 --> 00:14:37,781
You said we'd go to Viera together
and hang out in the evening!

167
00:14:52,413 --> 00:14:55,048
Seol Nae Il, where are you going?
You have no money!

168
00:15:07,866 --> 00:15:10,460
Maestro Viera is not there?

169
00:15:12,161 --> 00:15:15,834
It can't be. I made an appointment with him.

170
00:15:15,834 --> 00:15:19,209
His program in Berlin changed.

171
00:15:19,209 --> 00:15:24,000
I'll call you when his schedule is settled.

172
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:26,788
Yes, okay.

173
00:15:33,350 --> 00:15:37,737
Orabang, we won't get to see Professor Viera?

174
00:15:39,182 --> 00:15:40,358
No.

175
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:45,417
But now you're in Europe,

176
00:15:45,417 --> 00:15:48,709
you can meet him anytime you want to.

177
00:15:48,709 --> 00:15:50,437
Right?

178
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:55,167
I guess I have no choice.

179
00:15:55,167 --> 00:15:57,778
I'll have to make the sacrifice.

180
00:15:58,573 --> 00:16:02,274
I'll definitely make you feel good, Orabang.

181
00:16:02,274 --> 00:16:04,584
What are you going to do?

182
00:16:04,584 --> 00:16:07,292
We will go sightseeing!

183
00:16:07,292 --> 00:16:10,417
Since it turned out this way,
let's have fun today!

184
00:16:10,417 --> 00:16:12,334
Sightseeing? You're using me as an excuse!

185
00:16:12,334 --> 00:16:13,459
Aren't you going to practice?

186
00:16:13,459 --> 00:16:17,756
We were going to hang out
after visiting Professor Viera anyway.

187
00:16:33,243 --> 00:16:35,003
Sunbae, look at this!

188
00:16:40,918 --> 00:16:43,220
Hello, Mozart!

189
00:17:10,906 --> 00:17:13,041
Mozart chocolate!

190
00:17:14,202 --> 00:17:19,381
I want to eat Mozart chocolate.
Just buy me one, please!

191
00:17:23,793 --> 00:17:25,667
This is so delicious.

192
00:17:25,667 --> 00:17:29,744
You seem more moved by Mozart chocolate
than Mozart's house.

193
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:32,626
They didn't even let me play the piano.

194
00:17:32,626 --> 00:17:35,000
Food that can't be eaten,
a piano that can't be played?

195
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:37,544
Useless.

196
00:17:41,519 --> 00:17:43,375
Orabang, say "ah".

197
00:17:43,375 --> 00:17:44,759
I don't want to.

198
00:17:47,025 --> 00:17:48,743
Still?

199
00:17:52,062 --> 00:17:54,490
You keep embarrassing me, so I'll eat one.

200
00:18:01,310 --> 00:18:03,876
Isn't it delicious? Delicious? Delicious?

201
00:18:03,876 --> 00:18:05,906
- Tell me it's delicious.
- Why did you buy so much?

202
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:11,709
I bought them for gifts.
The best part of a honeymoon is shopping.

203
00:18:11,709 --> 00:18:13,876
Honeymoon!

204
00:18:13,876 --> 00:18:15,498
Honeymoon?

205
00:18:17,743 --> 00:18:20,959
Chocolate or piano,
you did everything you wanted to do.

206
00:18:20,959 --> 00:18:22,672
So now go practice your piano.

207
00:18:23,767 --> 00:18:26,543
We've come this far,
so we should at least go to Hellbrunn Palace.

208
00:18:26,543 --> 00:18:27,918
What are you talking about?

209
00:18:27,918 --> 00:18:30,180
What are you talking about? No!

210
00:18:34,343 --> 00:18:35,918
Orabang!

211
00:18:35,918 --> 00:18:39,000
Did you eat something bad for lunch?

212
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,626
Didn't you see Sound of Music?

213
00:18:40,626 --> 00:18:44,042
The palace
where Captain von Trapp proposed to Maria!

214
00:18:44,042 --> 00:18:45,375
The place of love

215
00:18:45,375 --> 00:18:48,440
where Liesl and her boyfriend whispered love
to each other!

216
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:51,159
Let's share our love in that palace.

217
00:20:08,917 --> 00:20:10,510
Seol Nae Il.

218
00:20:12,488 --> 00:20:14,290
Why, Orabang?

219
00:20:15,485 --> 00:20:18,417
You don't want to go home, do you?

220
00:20:18,417 --> 00:20:20,610
I have something to give to you,
so close your eyes.

221
00:20:21,709 --> 00:20:22,917
What is it?

222
00:20:28,187 --> 00:20:30,489
Pull your lips back.

223
00:20:41,783 --> 00:20:43,793
Open your eyes!

224
00:21:04,056 --> 00:21:05,441
What the...

225
00:21:13,941 --> 00:21:15,617
I'm losing my mind.

226
00:21:23,033 --> 00:21:28,213
Orabang, you wanted to drench me in water?

227
00:21:33,042 --> 00:21:36,667
Orabang? Orabang!

228
00:21:36,667 --> 00:21:40,078
Orabang, where are you? Ora...

229
00:21:41,718 --> 00:21:44,312
Orabang, are you looking for something?

230
00:21:52,353 --> 00:21:55,523
You took revenge on me
because I wouldn't practice the piano?

231
00:21:55,523 --> 00:21:59,876
I didn't know you were so narrow-minded!

232
00:21:59,876 --> 00:22:01,876
Should we just leave then?

233
00:22:01,876 --> 00:22:05,209
Sure, I'll just give up.

234
00:22:05,209 --> 00:22:07,209
I'll never buy them again.

235
00:22:07,209 --> 00:22:10,900
What? What did you lose? What did you buy?

236
00:22:12,537 --> 00:22:14,172
Rings.

237
00:22:15,127 --> 00:22:20,307
Round, pretty rings that you really wanted.

238
00:22:24,250 --> 00:22:26,795
No! My round, pretty rings!

239
00:22:26,795 --> 00:22:28,918
I have to find my rings!

240
00:22:28,918 --> 00:22:30,640
I have to find the rings!

241
00:22:32,027 --> 00:22:33,083
Where are you going?

242
00:22:33,083 --> 00:22:36,062
Step aside. Step aside. Step aside!

243
00:22:36,772 --> 00:22:40,000
Rings, where are you? My rings.

244
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,459
Let's just go. You wanted to leave.

245
00:22:41,459 --> 00:22:44,822
No! I won't leave until I find the rings!

246
00:22:44,822 --> 00:22:46,876
Aren't you going to practice?

247
00:22:46,876 --> 00:22:50,076
Couple rings come first!
I won't leave until I find them!

248
00:22:53,113 --> 00:22:55,832
The completion of love is couple rings!

249
00:22:56,864 --> 00:22:58,368
What do you know?

250
00:22:59,503 --> 00:23:01,340
You don't even know.

251
00:23:02,992 --> 00:23:05,377
Where did they go?

252
00:23:11,506 --> 00:23:13,641
- I'm not leaving!
- Here.

253
00:23:21,607 --> 00:23:23,959
Orabang, now give it to me.

254
00:23:23,959 --> 00:23:25,885
The couple ring...

255
00:23:30,911 --> 00:23:32,712
- You want this, right?
- Yes.

256
00:23:34,540 --> 00:23:37,510
The competition comes first.
I'll give it to you if you win.

257
00:23:41,002 --> 00:23:42,495
Should we go practice now?

258
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:45,876
Yes, let's go practice.

259
00:23:45,876 --> 00:23:47,091
Let's go.

260
00:23:51,007 --> 00:23:54,891
I'm going to look for a place
after Nae Il's competition is over.

261
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:58,772
Don't worry.

262
00:23:58,792 --> 00:24:00,438
I'll take care of it.

263
00:24:03,057 --> 00:24:05,985
Go to bed, Mom. It's early morning there.

264
00:24:07,830 --> 00:24:09,840
Okay, good night.

265
00:24:28,844 --> 00:24:30,228
What?

266
00:24:31,682 --> 00:24:36,028
I can't fall asleep
and I'm not feeling well either.

267
00:24:36,518 --> 00:24:39,613
Did I get too wet earlier?

268
00:24:46,945 --> 00:24:48,955
You have no fever.

269
00:24:50,584 --> 00:24:55,834
Then it's probably not a cold,

270
00:24:55,834 --> 00:24:59,872
but I keep thinking about Mom and my friends.

271
00:25:00,860 --> 00:25:03,663
Is this called homesick?

272
00:25:09,540 --> 00:25:11,459
I was there for you

273
00:25:11,459 --> 00:25:14,918
when you were scared
like a puppy on the plane.

274
00:25:14,918 --> 00:25:18,516
I patted and relieved you.

275
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:22,588
I did that for you.

276
00:25:23,857 --> 00:25:25,700
I'm disappointed.

277
00:25:30,411 --> 00:25:31,879
Come in.

278
00:25:34,952 --> 00:25:36,548
I'm so sick.

279
00:25:40,874 --> 00:25:42,550
It's so cold.

280
00:25:51,192 --> 00:25:53,668
By the way, do you have anything to eat?

281
00:25:54,470 --> 00:25:56,429
I'm hungry.

282
00:25:58,599 --> 00:26:00,484
I don't.

283
00:26:01,259 --> 00:26:05,334
I want something spicy like ramen,
don't you have any?

284
00:26:05,334 --> 00:26:10,167
If you go to a store in front,
would they have it?

285
00:26:10,167 --> 00:26:12,395
Would they? Would they not?

286
00:26:12,395 --> 00:26:13,863
Stay here.

287
00:26:18,370 --> 00:26:21,715
It hurts. It's cold.

288
00:26:33,218 --> 00:26:35,770
What's good for a cold?

289
00:26:39,154 --> 00:26:40,788
Honey.

290
00:26:42,309 --> 00:26:43,604
Okay.

291
00:26:44,771 --> 00:26:46,156
Ramen!

292
00:26:51,985 --> 00:26:54,500
Mini Min Hee, take a careful look.

293
00:26:54,500 --> 00:26:56,364
First one.

294
00:26:57,699 --> 00:26:59,459
Does it look good on me?

295
00:26:59,459 --> 00:27:01,000
Then what about this one?

296
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:03,780
Tada! Second one.

297
00:27:03,780 --> 00:27:07,042
Are you really sharing a room with Sunbae?

298
00:27:07,042 --> 00:27:10,244
Of course.
We're already like a husband and a wife.

299
00:27:10,244 --> 00:27:12,542
We'll be studying abroad together,

300
00:27:12,542 --> 00:27:15,375
so we decided
to practice being a married couple.

301
00:27:15,375 --> 00:27:16,626
Really?

302
00:27:16,626 --> 00:27:19,379
- Sunbae wanted to do that?
- That's what I said!

303
00:27:19,379 --> 00:27:22,640
Feel free to spread rumors all you want.

304
00:27:24,685 --> 00:27:26,083
What about this one?

305
00:27:26,083 --> 00:27:27,561
Is it sexy?

306
00:27:29,189 --> 00:27:33,111
By the way,
why does Sunbae look angry behind you?

307
00:27:41,036 --> 00:27:43,421
Sunbae, you're already back?

308
00:27:44,621 --> 00:27:46,792
I was worried about you.

309
00:27:46,792 --> 00:27:48,167
Get out.

310
00:27:48,167 --> 00:27:50,417
- Get out! Hurry up!
- Oh no, I'm sick.

311
00:27:50,417 --> 00:27:52,500
- Damn it! Get out!
- No. Mini Min Hee!

312
00:27:52,500 --> 00:27:54,083
- I knew it.
- Help me!

313
00:27:54,083 --> 00:27:56,165
Mini Min Hee, help me!

314
00:27:56,165 --> 00:27:57,792
Get out now!

315
00:27:57,792 --> 00:28:00,334
No, Sunbae! You shouldn't do this!

316
00:28:00,334 --> 00:28:01,292
Mini Min Hee!

317
00:28:01,292 --> 00:28:03,792
- Get out! Get out!
- I'm really sick.

318
00:28:03,792 --> 00:28:06,584
You're forbidden to come here
until the competition is over.

319
00:28:06,584 --> 00:28:08,542
I won't spread rumors again. I'm sorry.

320
00:28:08,542 --> 00:28:10,471
You weren't telling me the truth anyway.

321
00:28:10,471 --> 00:28:13,417
If you have time for tricks, practice.

322
00:28:13,417 --> 00:28:15,359
Please don't do this!

323
00:28:20,701 --> 00:28:25,089
I shouldn't have made the call.
I should've just pretended to be sick.

324
00:28:27,620 --> 00:28:30,167
I'm so sick, I don't think I can sleep alone.

325
00:28:30,167 --> 00:28:32,084
I'm really sick.

326
00:28:37,764 --> 00:28:41,125
Before you leave,
should we wear couple shirts?

327
00:28:41,125 --> 00:28:42,959
Or should get couple shoes?

328
00:28:42,959 --> 00:28:45,334
Forget it. What couple shirts?
Like little kids...

329
00:28:45,334 --> 00:28:47,167
Why? How is that for kids?

330
00:28:47,167 --> 00:28:50,052
Then like mature adults,

331
00:28:50,052 --> 00:28:53,042
how about couple underwear?

332
00:28:53,042 --> 00:28:54,417
Don't go overboard!

333
00:28:54,417 --> 00:28:56,459
Why? Isn't it nice to have couple underwear?

334
00:28:56,459 --> 00:28:58,736
- Forget it.
- I agree.

335
00:29:01,395 --> 00:29:04,125
Why do you have a date here?

336
00:29:04,125 --> 00:29:05,834
Go far away or somewhere else.

337
00:29:05,834 --> 00:29:07,125
Is this the only place to go?

338
00:29:07,125 --> 00:29:09,709
Il Lak said that he needs to help his father.

339
00:29:09,709 --> 00:29:12,000
He says he doesn't have time all day.

340
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:17,500
Oh, and Il Lak got this for you.

341
00:29:17,500 --> 00:29:20,000
Make sure to take three glasses a day.

342
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,009
Right, Il Lak?

343
00:29:22,095 --> 00:29:23,396
What?

344
00:29:28,767 --> 00:29:32,312
You really shouldn't have.

345
00:29:32,312 --> 00:29:35,167
It's hard to find a filial son
like Il Lak these days.

346
00:29:35,167 --> 00:29:37,775
He even takes care of his father's health.

347
00:29:39,403 --> 00:29:41,042
We'll hang out just a little longer
and help you.

348
00:29:41,042 --> 00:29:43,626
Don't worry about helping me. Just hang out.

349
00:29:43,626 --> 00:29:45,533
That's how you can help me.

350
00:29:46,954 --> 00:29:48,839
Have fun.

351
00:29:51,697 --> 00:29:53,407
Why did you buy that?

352
00:29:53,407 --> 00:29:54,792
I bought it on my way here.

353
00:29:54,792 --> 00:29:55,876
I feel bad.

354
00:29:55,876 --> 00:29:57,920
Don't worry.

355
00:30:02,928 --> 00:30:08,025
She's considerate just like Il Lak's mom.

356
00:30:49,097 --> 00:30:50,542
Viola.

357
00:30:50,542 --> 00:30:52,717
Tremolo in Letter A is difficult, right?

358
00:30:52,717 --> 00:30:55,375
We'll just go with 16th notes there.

359
00:30:55,375 --> 00:30:57,104
Don't slow down too much, Bass.

360
00:30:59,167 --> 00:31:01,250
Let's take 10 minutes and continue.

361
00:31:01,250 --> 00:31:03,569
Your lips shouldn't get too relaxed
for wind instruments.

362
00:31:30,923 --> 00:31:33,517
Your participation is confirmed.
Take your card, please.

363
00:31:35,894 --> 00:31:38,584
It'll decide when you'll perform.

364
00:31:38,584 --> 00:31:39,688
Pick one.

365
00:31:41,999 --> 00:31:46,804
Which one should I choose?
Make a guess, ding dong dang!

366
00:31:51,292 --> 00:31:52,584
It's number 12.

367
00:31:52,584 --> 00:31:54,119
It's the last one.

368
00:31:56,862 --> 00:32:00,042
Check your time for rehearsal and concert.
Please don't be late.

369
00:32:00,042 --> 00:32:02,125
Okay. Where is the stage?

370
00:32:02,125 --> 00:32:03,417
That way.

371
00:32:03,417 --> 00:32:04,797
Thank you.

372
00:32:06,642 --> 00:32:10,571
Okay, thank you. Thank you.
Thank you very much!

373
00:32:12,474 --> 00:32:14,901
I guess someone is practicing.

374
00:33:11,033 --> 00:33:12,918
She's Lu Wei.

375
00:33:14,075 --> 00:33:18,209
Lu Wei. Do you know her?

376
00:33:18,209 --> 00:33:20,873
She's a pianist who had a recital in Korea.

377
00:33:23,011 --> 00:33:24,729
So why is she here?

378
00:33:25,536 --> 00:33:26,959
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

379
00:33:26,959 --> 00:33:29,540
Is Lu Wei also a contestant for this contest?

380
00:33:29,540 --> 00:33:31,675
Yes, she is. You didn't know?

381
00:33:35,224 --> 00:33:40,070
So I have to do better than her
to win the competition?

382
00:33:50,987 --> 00:33:53,209
Do you see the cathedral over there?

383
00:33:53,867 --> 00:33:55,660
I'm going to find one behind it.

384
00:33:57,109 --> 00:33:58,575
Our house...

385
00:34:00,497 --> 00:34:02,214
that we'll live in.

386
00:34:05,409 --> 00:34:07,000
I see.

387
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:09,671
That's your house that you will live in.

388
00:34:11,356 --> 00:34:15,211
You'll eat there
and read the score there too.

389
00:34:15,211 --> 00:34:16,970
By yourself, Orabang.

390
00:34:19,226 --> 00:34:20,611
Seol Nae Il.

391
00:34:22,510 --> 00:34:28,107
I wanted to make you food
that could really help you.

392
00:34:29,304 --> 00:34:32,561
I memorized a whole recipe on eel,
but I won't even get to use it.

393
00:34:32,561 --> 00:34:35,083
Why do you worry about losing?
That's not like you.

394
00:34:35,083 --> 00:34:38,534
If I don't win,
I have to leave you behind and go back!

395
00:34:41,123 --> 00:34:46,834
Yes, if you don't win,
I'll have to stay by myself.

396
00:34:46,834 --> 00:34:48,619
In my house over there.

397
00:34:48,619 --> 00:34:50,375
Are you already thinking
about living by yourself?

398
00:34:50,375 --> 00:34:51,542
Without me?

399
00:34:51,542 --> 00:34:53,632
Why? Just why?

400
00:34:54,303 --> 00:34:55,937
Seriously.

401
00:34:58,891 --> 00:35:01,693
You're going to cheat on me
with blond sisters, right?

402
00:35:02,267 --> 00:35:05,334
Blonds? Maybe.

403
00:35:05,334 --> 00:35:06,751
Player!

404
00:35:06,751 --> 00:35:08,918
How long has it been
since you gave me a hug from behind?

405
00:35:08,918 --> 00:35:10,792
Don't you even remember?

406
00:35:10,792 --> 00:35:13,626
But who's going to hit on me?

407
00:35:13,626 --> 00:35:17,739
You'll be stuck to me
like a piece of gum 24-7.

408
00:35:22,372 --> 00:35:23,840
That's what you'll do.

409
00:35:24,684 --> 00:35:27,320
You'll stay with me forever.

410
00:35:30,100 --> 00:35:33,445
This place is full of geniuses.

411
00:35:35,093 --> 00:35:36,644
Still...

412
00:35:51,026 --> 00:35:52,827
I was going to give it to you after you win.

413
00:35:54,205 --> 00:35:55,751
Orabang.

414
00:35:55,751 --> 00:35:57,271
My goodness.

415
00:35:58,459 --> 00:35:59,918
Take it.

416
00:35:59,918 --> 00:36:02,075
It's your charm to help you win.

417
00:36:03,459 --> 00:36:05,253
I just can't.

418
00:36:05,253 --> 00:36:07,138
My God.

419
00:36:22,558 --> 00:36:24,776
Now you can win, right?

420
00:36:34,570 --> 00:36:36,276
No.

421
00:36:36,986 --> 00:36:39,155
I can't win with this.

422
00:36:39,155 --> 00:36:40,083
What?

423
00:36:40,083 --> 00:36:42,767
Just a ring won't do it.

424
00:36:44,955 --> 00:36:49,467
I need a victory kiss to win or something.

425
00:36:59,083 --> 00:37:00,918
Go away.

426
00:37:00,918 --> 00:37:04,346
Orabang! A victory kiss!
Don't you know about kisses?

427
00:37:09,584 --> 00:37:11,000
No!

428
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:13,167
Orabang! What's wrong?

429
00:37:13,167 --> 00:37:15,440
Let's kiss!

430
00:37:17,654 --> 00:37:20,248
Just give me a proper, deep one.

431
00:37:24,995 --> 00:37:26,671
Orabang!

432
00:37:38,590 --> 00:37:42,709
Her name on the application is not consistent
with the name on the passport.

433
00:37:42,709 --> 00:37:45,584
In this case,
we can't confirm her identification

434
00:37:45,584 --> 00:37:47,873
and she cannot be in the contest.

435
00:37:49,550 --> 00:37:52,500
I will correct the spelling right now.

436
00:37:52,500 --> 00:37:55,459
You can't correct the application
once it's submitted.

437
00:37:55,459 --> 00:37:59,626
You can't just disqualify her
for wrong spelling.

438
00:37:59,626 --> 00:38:01,403
It is regulation.

439
00:38:05,508 --> 00:38:08,519
Seol Nae Il needs to prove
that she's Seol Nae Il?

440
00:38:09,329 --> 00:38:11,542
The English spelling on her application
is different from her passport?

441
00:38:11,542 --> 00:38:13,834
How could she make that mistake?

442
00:38:13,834 --> 00:38:16,334
Okay, I'll look into it.

443
00:38:16,334 --> 00:38:19,756
What? Did something happen
to Yoo Jin and Nae Il?

444
00:38:19,756 --> 00:38:23,184
Let's go to Seoul first.
I'll explain it to you on the way.

445
00:38:38,876 --> 00:38:40,961
Yoon Hoo!

446
00:38:40,961 --> 00:38:42,721
It's time for our rehearsal on stage.

447
00:39:02,801 --> 00:39:05,354
Verdi's La Forza del Destino.

448
00:39:06,167 --> 00:39:10,722
It is resolute but also majestic,
just like the composer's spirit.

449
00:39:12,674 --> 00:39:16,292
Verdi gave up music
because of political pressure

450
00:39:16,292 --> 00:39:20,523
but he got himself back up
as he was composing La Forza del Destino.

451
00:39:21,584 --> 00:39:25,186
This music became Verdi's reason to live on.

452
00:39:25,186 --> 00:39:29,000
What does this music mean to me right now?

453
00:39:51,808 --> 00:39:53,568
Nae Il.

454
00:39:54,334 --> 00:39:58,178
Will you play a duet with me?

455
00:39:58,178 --> 00:40:00,709
Why me?

456
00:40:00,709 --> 00:40:03,483
I want to perform
with your piano accompaniment.

457
00:40:04,757 --> 00:40:06,542
Today's performance...

458
00:40:06,542 --> 00:40:09,250
is about sending off my 20 years friendship.

459
00:40:09,250 --> 00:40:11,608
You think your injury is none of my business?

460
00:40:11,608 --> 00:40:14,410
If I really like it, I'd never give up.

461
00:40:59,209 --> 00:41:02,334
This is the principle
of Han Eum Music Academy.

462
00:41:02,334 --> 00:41:06,629
I am aware that there is a mistake, however...

463
00:41:42,375 --> 00:41:44,834
Hello? Did you check everything?

464
00:41:44,834 --> 00:41:46,667
Are you sure?

465
00:41:46,667 --> 00:41:48,417
Keep looking!

466
00:41:48,417 --> 00:41:49,630
Okay.

467
00:41:50,792 --> 00:41:54,212
Please. Let us just sign and submit.

468
00:41:54,212 --> 00:41:56,548
I can't ignore our regulation.

469
00:41:56,548 --> 00:41:59,709
We just cannot give up after coming this far.

470
00:41:59,709 --> 00:42:01,561
Sorry.

471
00:42:39,424 --> 00:42:43,686
I played hard to get,
acting as if I didn't want to come but...

472
00:42:46,711 --> 00:42:49,263
I guess Seol Nae Il deserves this.

473
00:44:06,352 --> 00:44:08,250
You need to bring a person

474
00:44:08,250 --> 00:44:12,626
who will identify and guarantee
that she's Seol Nae Il.

475
00:44:12,626 --> 00:44:15,459
And that guarantor should be
one of the judges

476
00:44:15,459 --> 00:44:19,115
or someone who is recognizeable
by the judges.

477
00:44:33,671 --> 00:44:36,125
I didn't mean to eavesdrop.

478
00:44:36,125 --> 00:44:39,385
I was curious
as to who was playing the piano.

479
00:44:41,459 --> 00:44:43,918
Are you a contestant in the competition?

480
00:44:43,918 --> 00:44:45,918
Yes.

481
00:44:45,918 --> 00:44:50,292
But I won't get to participate.

482
00:44:50,292 --> 00:44:53,811
You won't get to participate? Why?

483
00:44:54,459 --> 00:44:59,256
By any chance,
are you the pianist Cha Dong Woo...

484
00:44:59,989 --> 00:45:03,667
I mean, are you Yoo Jin Sunbae's father?

485
00:45:03,667 --> 00:45:06,312
How do you know my son?

486
00:45:11,626 --> 00:45:13,834
How do you do?

487
00:45:13,834 --> 00:45:16,263
I'm Yoo Jin Sunbae's...

488
00:45:33,233 --> 00:45:37,329
How did you get here?

489
00:45:56,840 --> 00:46:01,686
Now I see that you're here,
your fear of flying must be cured.

490
00:46:02,952 --> 00:46:05,421
- Yes.
- How did you cure it?

491
00:46:06,808 --> 00:46:10,862
I didn't know
you'd be curious about the process.

492
00:46:15,317 --> 00:46:18,620
Right, the process is not important.

493
00:46:19,902 --> 00:46:22,079
Tell me what you're going to do now.

494
00:46:23,283 --> 00:46:27,420
Seol Nae Il, the girl you just saw...

495
00:46:29,706 --> 00:46:32,133
I want to study with her.

496
00:46:36,585 --> 00:46:39,125
I didn't see your name
on the contestants' list.

497
00:46:39,125 --> 00:46:41,500
So I wondered why you were here.

498
00:46:41,500 --> 00:46:43,626
You came to support your girlfriend?

499
00:46:43,626 --> 00:46:45,834
It's important to prepare for my study,

500
00:46:45,834 --> 00:46:49,918
but my priority is her competition.

501
00:46:49,918 --> 00:46:53,417
Aren't you embarrassed for saying that?

502
00:46:53,417 --> 00:46:59,792
Your priority must always be
your music and your future.

503
00:46:59,792 --> 00:47:01,786
That's why.

504
00:47:02,307 --> 00:47:06,403
Because she's the one I can lean on
and stay together.

505
00:47:08,792 --> 00:47:11,459
There is no "together" in this path.

506
00:47:11,459 --> 00:47:13,709
Being alone is already too much.

507
00:47:13,709 --> 00:47:15,443
Do it yourself,

508
00:47:16,709 --> 00:47:19,561
or find someone
who will adjust everything for you.

509
00:47:22,342 --> 00:47:26,604
I won't live that way.

510
00:47:32,269 --> 00:47:34,029
It looks that way.

511
00:47:41,987 --> 00:47:46,875
Rachmaninoff wasn't bad last time.

512
00:47:48,001 --> 00:47:52,389
For a college orchestra,
it was okay to listen to.

513
00:48:08,555 --> 00:48:11,211
So this is how it feels

514
00:48:12,834 --> 00:48:15,177
to hear my father's compliment.

515
00:48:19,048 --> 00:48:23,792
The list of judges
for the Salzburg Competition

516
00:48:23,792 --> 00:48:26,189
is top secret.

517
00:48:27,496 --> 00:48:30,417
You can only find out
after the competition is over.

518
00:48:30,417 --> 00:48:33,760
Do you mean
that I can't contact them before that?

519
00:48:36,463 --> 00:48:39,516
Nothing comes easy for Baby.

520
00:48:40,251 --> 00:48:42,500
I'll look into it,

521
00:48:42,500 --> 00:48:47,649
but even if I get the list,
it won't be easy to meet them.

522
00:48:52,042 --> 00:48:54,565
You don't know who the judges are yet?

523
00:48:54,565 --> 00:48:57,083
Just wait.

524
00:48:57,083 --> 00:48:59,361
I'm also waiting right now.

525
00:48:59,361 --> 00:49:02,000
We'll begin soon.

526
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:04,541
Even if someone guarantees her identity,
it'll be too late.

527
00:49:05,000 --> 00:49:08,167
It's not just you who is in a hurry.

528
00:49:08,167 --> 00:49:09,796
I'm sorry.

529
00:49:11,949 --> 00:49:13,959
It's fine now.

530
00:49:13,959 --> 00:49:16,167
We tried everything we could,
but it's not working out.

531
00:49:16,167 --> 00:49:19,209
I heard it means
that we should wait for the next chance.

532
00:49:19,209 --> 00:49:22,059
- So now...
- I haven't done everything I could.

533
00:49:25,542 --> 00:49:28,292
Miss Seol Nae Il, you're in the contest.

534
00:49:28,292 --> 00:49:29,626
How on earth?

535
00:49:29,626 --> 00:49:33,584
One of the judges has just confirmed
her identification.

536
00:49:33,584 --> 00:49:35,264
Please follow me.

537
00:50:18,977 --> 00:50:23,281
Cha Dong Woo is one of the judges.

538
00:50:24,083 --> 00:50:26,167
My father is a judge?

539
00:50:26,167 --> 00:50:29,513
If it's the Cha Dong Woo that I know,
no way.

540
00:50:30,173 --> 00:50:33,417
But if it's his son's request,
maybe it's possible.

541
00:50:33,417 --> 00:50:37,646
If it's the father that I know,
it won't work at all.

542
00:50:40,340 --> 00:50:43,977
Rachmaninoff wasn't bad last time.

543
00:50:45,483 --> 00:50:49,120
For a college orchestra,
it was okay to listen to.

544
00:50:53,634 --> 00:50:55,005
But...

545
00:50:56,014 --> 00:50:58,378
he seems to have changed a little

546
00:50:59,667 --> 00:51:01,726
from how I remember him.

547
00:51:30,542 --> 00:51:33,011
Is it my turn soon?

548
00:51:33,930 --> 00:51:35,064
Yes.

549
00:51:37,042 --> 00:51:38,918
Don't think about anything else.

550
00:51:38,918 --> 00:51:42,847
Just think that you're playing
in your own room.

551
00:51:44,938 --> 00:51:50,284
It's my room, it's my room.
I'm playing in my room.

552
00:51:55,782 --> 00:51:59,377
To be honest, I don't need to win anymore.

553
00:52:01,334 --> 00:52:05,346
It's about showing people
the pianist Seol Nae Il.

554
00:52:07,374 --> 00:52:09,334
Do you mean that?

555
00:52:09,334 --> 00:52:10,643
Yes.

556
00:52:14,611 --> 00:52:18,344
By the way, did they call my name?

557
00:52:19,014 --> 00:52:20,733
Did they?

558
00:52:22,788 --> 00:52:24,757
No, they didn't.

559
00:52:25,417 --> 00:52:27,417
You said you didn't need to win.

560
00:52:27,417 --> 00:52:30,597
Still, I want to win.

561
00:52:37,699 --> 00:52:39,875
You'll do well.

562
00:52:43,396 --> 00:52:46,615
Miss Seol Nae Il, it's your turn now.

563
00:53:12,109 --> 00:53:15,954
As a butterfly's flutter
can cause a thunderstorm,

564
00:53:16,947 --> 00:53:21,031
there are times
when trivial things change everything.

565
00:53:22,399 --> 00:53:25,911
The piano sound
that resonated in the garbage dumpster.

566
00:53:27,187 --> 00:53:29,072
Without that morning,

567
00:53:29,626 --> 00:53:32,971
where would we be now?

568
00:55:33,288 --> 00:55:37,834
Sunbae, I finally get to go study abroad!

569
00:55:37,834 --> 00:55:39,527
Congratulations, Nae Il!

570
00:55:39,527 --> 00:55:41,751
I'll give you a hug. Come here.

571
00:55:41,751 --> 00:55:44,792
No, a hug is not enough.

572
00:55:44,792 --> 00:55:46,959
I need a kiss of love.

573
00:55:46,959 --> 00:55:48,753
You do?

574
00:55:54,736 --> 00:55:56,334
Playing pitiful again?

575
00:55:56,334 --> 00:55:58,679
Seriously.

576
00:55:59,918 --> 00:56:02,637
Yoo Jin Sunbae hasn't contacted you?

577
00:56:04,184 --> 00:56:06,387
He hasn't called me yet.

578
00:56:06,387 --> 00:56:08,876
You said you were packing today.

579
00:56:08,876 --> 00:56:11,518
I'll just pack by myself.

580
00:56:11,518 --> 00:56:13,042
How will you pack alone?

581
00:56:13,042 --> 00:56:14,584
Wait until I get back.

582
00:56:14,584 --> 00:56:16,648
Don't play pitifully alone again.

583
00:56:16,648 --> 00:56:19,417
Really? You'll come and pack with me?

584
00:56:19,417 --> 00:56:21,528
Mini Min Hee. Mini Min Hee.

585
00:56:21,528 --> 00:56:23,079
I'm not going.

586
00:56:24,366 --> 00:56:25,657
Sorry.

587
00:56:25,657 --> 00:56:29,417
I hear we'll get many students
worthy of our training next year.

588
00:56:29,417 --> 00:56:31,834
- I'm getting very excited.
- Me too.

589
00:56:31,834 --> 00:56:35,042
A lot of students seem to flock to our school
because of good school spirit.

590
00:56:35,042 --> 00:56:37,334
I don't welcome students

591
00:56:37,334 --> 00:56:39,042
who come here
because they like relaxing atmospheres.

592
00:56:39,042 --> 00:56:41,459
You like having fun, too.

593
00:56:41,459 --> 00:56:44,100
It was obvious
when you completed the Fart Song.

594
00:56:45,292 --> 00:56:47,918
It's was only to educate Seol Nae Il.

595
00:56:47,918 --> 00:56:49,856
But you still had fun, right?

596
00:56:50,765 --> 00:56:53,067
It wasn't bad.

597
00:56:59,086 --> 00:57:03,474
I'm working on funding Rising Star
as a professional orchestra.

598
00:57:06,488 --> 00:57:09,617
It'll be the same even after they graduate?

599
00:57:09,617 --> 00:57:14,417
After the initial support,
they'll find their place soon.

600
00:57:14,417 --> 00:57:17,125
I'll need to convince the alumni,

601
00:57:17,125 --> 00:57:18,918
but it'll work out.

602
00:57:18,918 --> 00:57:24,807
They're going forward one step at a time
on their own.

603
00:57:31,097 --> 00:57:35,000
Stop worrying about the students
who are doing well on their own.

604
00:57:35,000 --> 00:57:40,042
Now, let's talk about us.

605
00:57:40,042 --> 00:57:42,909
About what we'll do together in the future.

606
00:57:52,083 --> 00:57:54,459
Guys, did you hear?

607
00:57:54,459 --> 00:57:55,709
What?

608
00:57:55,709 --> 00:57:58,792
Rising Star is a pro orchestra!
We can continue after graduation.

609
00:57:58,792 --> 00:58:00,394
What do you think? Isn't it awesome?

610
00:58:00,394 --> 00:58:01,876
Good!

611
00:58:01,876 --> 00:58:04,000
Our bandmaster really knows what he's doing.

612
00:58:04,000 --> 00:58:05,876
You're the best.

613
00:58:05,876 --> 00:58:07,209
The dean also wants us

614
00:58:07,209 --> 00:58:09,876
to become an example of success
without studying abroad.

615
00:58:09,876 --> 00:58:12,584
We don't need to make it so grand.

616
00:58:12,584 --> 00:58:13,876
We're having fun, right?

617
00:58:13,876 --> 00:58:16,167
Just continue like we have done.

618
00:58:16,167 --> 00:58:20,230
Before that, let's do a special concert.

619
00:58:20,230 --> 00:58:21,697
Special concert?

620
00:58:26,798 --> 00:58:28,975
Which one should I pack first?

621
00:58:30,114 --> 00:58:33,459
I have so many memories of Sunbae here.

622
00:58:33,459 --> 00:58:35,495
No! And this, too!

623
00:58:35,495 --> 00:58:38,167
How can I throw them out?

624
00:58:38,167 --> 00:58:39,500
Hey!

625
00:58:39,500 --> 00:58:41,209
Throw them all out!

626
00:58:41,209 --> 00:58:43,375
Are you going to keep packing and play pitiful
until you leave the country?

627
00:58:43,375 --> 00:58:46,459
Sunbae, how can I throw out my treasure?

628
00:58:46,459 --> 00:58:48,734
They were thrown out to begin with.

629
00:58:48,734 --> 00:58:52,512
I picked them up
because they were good enough to use.

630
00:58:52,512 --> 00:58:54,667
So don't pick up just anything.

631
00:58:54,667 --> 00:58:56,626
I said I'd pack by myself.
Why did you come?

632
00:58:56,626 --> 00:58:58,083
I knew you'd be like this.

633
00:58:58,083 --> 00:59:00,786
If you're going to pack all your trash,
cancel your study abroad.

634
00:59:01,354 --> 00:59:05,700
Sunbae, I can't.
How can I throw them all out? No!

635
00:59:07,002 --> 00:59:08,959
They're so precious to me.

636
00:59:08,959 --> 00:59:10,697
Sunbae, no!

637
00:59:10,697 --> 00:59:13,459
Hi, Mini Min Hee! Hi, Lak!
Hi, Mr. Curly Hair!

638
00:59:13,459 --> 00:59:14,918
Would the reporters write articles

639
00:59:14,918 --> 00:59:16,792
about how she'll become
the next idol of classical music

640
00:59:16,792 --> 00:59:17,667
after Son Soo Ji

641
00:59:17,667 --> 00:59:19,042
after seeing her like that?

642
00:59:19,042 --> 00:59:21,542
Should I just take a picture
and expose the truth?

643
00:59:21,542 --> 00:59:23,417
Leave it.

644
00:59:23,417 --> 00:59:26,459
Thanks to her,
our Rising Star got its name out, too.

645
00:59:26,459 --> 00:59:30,850
People usually change
after winning the Salzburg Competition.

646
00:59:32,135 --> 00:59:33,584
Why is she the same?

647
00:59:33,584 --> 00:59:35,542
- Useless!
- Help me!

648
00:59:35,542 --> 00:59:38,667
That's enough, Yoo Jin, Nae Il!

649
00:59:38,667 --> 00:59:40,709
You have somewhere to go with us.

650
00:59:40,709 --> 00:59:42,361
- Where?
- Where?

651
01:00:02,959 --> 01:00:07,000
When I didn't do anything, I wasn't anything.

652
01:00:07,000 --> 01:00:10,558
When I was alone, it was natural to be alone.

653
01:00:11,885 --> 01:00:14,345
As I met as many people
as the types of instruements

654
01:00:14,345 --> 01:00:18,083
and tuned their melody and created chords,

655
01:00:18,083 --> 01:00:23,070
I was able to see people in the world
where music was everything.

656
01:00:27,123 --> 01:00:33,459
We are still clumsy,
prone to falling and slow like a turtle,

657
01:00:33,459 --> 01:00:35,709
but we're learning
the meaning of the word "together"

658
01:00:35,709 --> 01:00:42,006
and following our own notes,
one step at a time.

659
01:00:48,922 --> 01:00:52,482
Soft and sweet.

660
01:00:52,482 --> 01:00:54,101
Cantabile.

661
01:00:54,721 --> 01:00:56,606
As if we're singing.
